headline: Data Center Momentum Fuels Breakout For This Top Performing S&P 500 Generator Play
summary: S&P 500 component Generac soared in stock market trade Wednesday, breaking out from a buy zone, despite missing fourth-quarter earnings estimates.  Generac, which provides backup power diesel generators for a wide range of applications — including data centers, announced early Wednesday that Q4 profit fell 42.5% to $1.61 per share with revenue declining 11% to $1.09 billion.  The S&P 500 generator play said Wednesday that it residential product sales decreased approximately 23% to $572 million, compared to $743 million last year.
